          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/by Authors/.Since Be-10 has a Life-Time of about",
                "1.0E+6 Years and hence does not necessarily decay to",
                "B-10 on Astrophysical Time Scale, it is in principle",
                "necessary to distinguish it from the other Mass-10",
                "Isobars.",
                "Thus the Present Measurements at 30.0 and 33.7 MeV are",
                "entirely unaffected and Be-10 contributes perhaps 4% of",
                "the Mass-10 Yield at the Higher Energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
